# Copilot Instructions for SpreadsheetUtilities

## Project Overview
- **Purpose**: Design pattern learning project + production-ready utility for single organization deployment
- **Targets**: .NET 8 & 9 (Blazor Server on .NET 9)
- **Deployment**: Azure Web App + Local development machines
- **Architecture**: Modular library-based design with multiple UI frontends

## Key Principles

### 1. Library Architecture
- **SpreadsheetUtility.Library** remains pure calculator/processor - NO UI concerns
- Constructor injection for all dependencies
- No static methods except Providers
- SOLID principles enforced
- No breaking changes to existing public interfaces without major version bump

### 2. Design Patterns
The codebase intentionally implements 11+ design patterns for learning:
- Observer, Strategy, Factory, Template Method, Builder, Facade
- Mapper/Adapter, Generic List Generator, Command, Dependency Injection, Provider
- **Do NOT remove patterns** - they are core to project's educational value
- Add new patterns when solving problems, not arbitrarily

### 3. Blazor Web Application (SpreadsheetUtility.UI.Web)
- **Framework**: Blazor Server (.NET 9)
- **Approach**: Interactive Server Components (not static SSR)
- Keep components simple and testable
- Separate concerns: UI Components ≠ Business Logic
- Use services for cross-component state

### 4. Backward Compatibility
- **Generate-from-paste behavior MUST remain** - core feature for power users
- Add file upload as ADDITIONAL option, not replacement
- Local folder reading is NEW enhancement
- Console apps continue working unchanged

## Development Workflow

### Code Standards
```csharp
// ✅ Good: Constructor injection, clear responsibility
public class GanttChartProcessor
{
    private readonly IGanttChartDataManager _dataManager;
    private readonly ILogger<GanttChartProcessor> _logger;

    public GanttChartProcessor(IGanttChartDataManager dataManager, ILogger<GanttChartProcessor> logger)
    {
        _dataManager = dataManager;
        _logger = logger;
    }
}

// ❌ Bad: Service locator, mixed concerns
public class BadProcessor
{
    public void Process() => ServiceLocator.Get<IService>().DoWork();
}
```

### Interface Naming
- **Services**: `I{ServiceName}` (e.g., `IGanttChartProcessor`)
- **Repositories**: `I{Entity}Repository` (e.g., `IProjectRepository`)
- **Strategies**: `I{Algorithm}Strategy` (e.g., `ITaskAssignmentStrategy`)
- **Factories**: `I{Component}Factory` (e.g., `ITaskAssignmentStrategyFactory`)
- **Managers**: `I{Domain}Manager` (e.g., `IGanttChartDataManager`)

### Testing
- Target library: **xUnit** (already in use)
- Mocking: **Moq** (already in use)
- Coverage goal: >80% for public APIs
- No unit tests for UI components yet (future: Bunit)
- Test naming: `[MethodName]_[Scenario]_[ExpectedOutcome]`

```csharp
[Fact]
public void CalculateWorkingDays_WithWeekend_ExcludesWeekendDays()
{
    // Arrange
    var calculator = new DateCalculator(...);

    // Act
    var result = calculator.CalculateWorkingDays(...);

    // Assert
    Assert.Equal(5, result);
}
```

## New Features: Architecture Guidelines

### Feature: User Authentication
- **New Project**: Optional - if adding, create `SpreadsheetUtility.Library.Identity`
- **Use**: Microsoft.AspNetCore.Identity + EF Core
- **Scope**: Single organization (no multi-tenant complexity)
- **UI**: Blazor pages only (no separate API initially)
- Keep authentication logic out of library project

### Feature: Data Persistence
- **Database**: SQL Server (Azure) or SQLite (local development)
- **ORM**: Entity Framework Core with migrations
- **New Project**: `SpreadsheetUtility.Library.DataAccess`
- **Patterns**: Repository + Unit of Work pattern
- **Library separation**: Library doesn't reference DataAccess - only UI does

### Feature: File Upload
- **Existing**: Paste behavior - KEEP
- **Add**: Excel/CSV file upload
- **Add**: Local folder reading (for batch processing)
- **Validation**: File type, size, format checking in UI layer
- **Processing**: Async operations with progress tracking

### New Extensions Method Organization
Create extension classes for cleaner Program.cs:
```csharp
// In new Extensions folder:
public static class ServiceCollectionExtensions
{
    public static IServiceCollection AddGanttServices(this IServiceCollection services) { ... }
    public static IServiceCollection AddAuthenticationServices(this IServiceCollection services) { ... }
    public static IServiceCollection AddDataAccessServices(this IServiceCollection services) { ... }
}

// In Program.cs:
builder.Services
    .AddGanttServices()
    .AddAuthenticationServices()
    .AddDataAccessServices();
```

