## Performance & Scalability

### Current Deployment Model
- Single organization, single Blazor Server app
- Session-per-user state management
- No distributed caching needed initially

### Future Considerations (Don't implement now)
- If scaling to multiple organizations: consider distributed sessions
- Large file processing: implement background job queue (Hangfire)
- Real-time updates: SignalR for multi-user scenarios

## Security Checklist

- [ ] No credentials in code (use Azure Key Vault / user-secrets)
- [ ] Validate all user inputs (file uploads, paste data)
- [ ] SQL injection prevention (EF Core parameterized queries)
- [ ] HTTPS only in production
- [ ] Secure session management
- [ ] CORS configured properly
- [ ] Authorization checks on all sensitive operations

## Dependencies Management

### Adding New NuGet Packages
1. Add only if necessary (check existing dependencies first)
2. Use LTS/stable versions
3. Document in CHANGELOG
4. Update minimum version requirements

### Current Dependencies Summary
- **Excel**: ClosedXML (MIT)
- **Testing**: xUnit, Moq
- **Logging**: Built-in Microsoft.Extensions.Logging
- **Serialization**: Newtonsoft.Json
- **Gantt Visualization**: Frappe Gantt (JavaScript)

